definition.value: A dihydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of (2,6-dihydroxyphenyl)acetic (homogentisic) acid, arising from deprotonation of the carboxy group.
A 4-hydroxy-3-polyprenylbenzoate in which the polyprenyl chain contains 8 prenyl units; major species at pH 7.3.
Elemental mercury of oxidation state zero.
A polyprenol diphosphate having neryl as the polyprenyl component.
